The paper deals with tracking algorithms for computer vision applications, specifically focusing on the problem of tracking points at object boundaries. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves shape-based matching and texture-based matching, which are common techniques in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The proposed algorithm also involves efficient tracking, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
